  ],
  "chapters": [
    {
      "id": "quran-1",
      "number": 1,
      "title": "Al-Fatiha (The Opening)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-1-1",
          "number": 1,
          "text": "In the name of Allah, the Entirely Merciful, the Especially Merciful.",
          "translation": "In the name of Allah, the Entirely Merciful, the Especially Merciful.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-1-2",
          "number": 2,
          "text": "All praise is due to Allah, Lord of the worlds.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-1-3",
          "number": 3,
          "text": "The Entirely Merciful, the Especially Merciful.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-1-4",
          "number": 4,
          "text": "Sovereign of the Day of Recompense.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-1-5",
          "number": 5,
          "text": "It is You we worship and You we ask for help.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-1-6",
          "number": 6,
          "text": "Guide us to the straight path.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-1-7",
          "number": 7,
          "text": "The path of those upon whom You have bestowed favor, not of those who have evoked [Your] anger or of those who are astray.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-2",
      "number": 2,
      "title": "Al-Baqarah (The Cow)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-2-255",
          "number": 255,
          "text": "Allah! There is no deity except Him, the Ever-Living, the Sustainer of existence. Neither drowsiness overtakes Him nor sleep. To Him belongs whatever is in the heavens and whatever is on the earth.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-2-256",
          "number": 256,
          "text": "There is no compulsion in religion. The right course has become distinct from the wrong.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-2-286",
          "number": 286,
          "text": "Allah does not charge a soul except [with that within] its capacity. It will have [the consequence of] what [good] it has gained, and it will bear [the consequence of] what [evil] it has earned.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-3",
      "number": 3,
      "title": "Ali 'Imran (The Family of Imran)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-3-185",
          "number": 185,
          "text": "Every soul will taste death, and you will only be given your full compensation on the Day of Resurrection.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-3-190",
          "number": 190,
          "text": "Indeed, in the creation of the heavens and the earth and the alternation of the night and the day are signs for those of understanding.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-3-191",
          "number": 191,
          "text": "Who remember Allah while standing or sitting or [lying] on their sides and give thought to the creation of the heavens and the earth, saying, 'Our Lord, You did not create this aimlessly.'",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-4",
      "number": 4,
      "title": "An-Nisa (The Women)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-4-1",
          "number": 1,
          "text": "O mankind, fear your Lord, who created you from one soul and created from it its mate and dispersed from both of them many men and women.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-4-135",
          "number": 135,
          "text": "O you who have believed, be persistently standing firm in justice, witnesses for Allah, even if it be against yourselves or parents and relatives.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-17",
      "number": 17,
      "title": "Al-Isra (The Night Journey)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-17-23",
          "number": 23,
          "text": "Your Lord has decre that you worship not except Him, and to parents, good treatment. Whether one or both of them reach old age [while] with you, say not to them [so much as], 'uff,' and do not repel them but speak to them a noble word.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-17-78",
          "number": 78,
          "text": "Establish prayer at the decline of the sun [from its meridian] until the darkness of the night and [also] the Quran [for] dawn. Indeed, the recitation of dawn is ever witnessed.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-23",
      "number": 23,
      "title": "Al-Mu'minun (The Believers)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-23-1",
          "number": 1,
          "text": "Successful indeed are the believers.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-23-115",
          "number": 115,
          "text": "Then did you think that We created you uselessly and that to Us you would not be returned?",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-29",
      "number": 29,
      "title": "Al-Ankabut (The Spider)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-29-2",
          "number": 2,
          "text": "Do the people think that they will be left to say, 'We believe' and they will not be tried?",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-29-69",
          "number": 69,
          "text": "And those who strive for Us - We will surely guide them to Our ways. Indeed, Allah is with the doers of good.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-49",
      "number": 49,
      "title": "Al-Hujurat (The Rooms)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-49-13",
          "number": 13,
          "text": "O mankind, indeed We have created you from male and female and made you peoples and tribes that you may know one another. Indeed, the most noble of you in the sight of Allah is the most righteous of you.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-55",
      "number": 55,
      "title": "Ar-Rahman (The Most Merciful)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-55-1",
          "number": 1,
          "text": "The Most Merciful.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-55-2",
          "number": 2,
          "text": "Taught the Quran.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-55-13",
          "number": 13,
          "text": "Then which of the favors of your Lord will you deny?",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-67",
      "number": 67,
      "title": "Al-Mulk (Dominion)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-67-1",
          "number": 1,
          "text": "Blessed is He in whose hand is dominion, and He is over all things competent.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-67-2",
          "number": 2,
          "text": "[He] who created death and life to test you [as to] which of you is best in deed.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-67-15",
          "number": 15,
          "text": "It is He who made the earth tame for you - so walk among its slopes and eat of His provision.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-93",
      "number": 93,
      "title": "Ad-Duha (The Morning Hours)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-93-1",
          "number": 1,
          "text": "By the morning hours.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-93-3",
          "number": 3,
          "text": "Your Lord has not taken leave of you, nor has He detested [you].",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-93-4",
          "number": 4,
          "text": "And the Hereafter is better for you than the present.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-93-5",
          "number": 5,
          "text": "And your Lord is going to give you, and you will be satisfied.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-94",
      "number": 94,
      "title": "Ash-Sharh (The Relief)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-94-5",
          "number": 5,
          "text": "For indeed, with hardship [will be] ease.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-94-6",
          "number": 6,
          "text": "Indeed, with hardship [will be] ease.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-94-7",
          "number": 7,
          "text": "So when you have finished [your duties], then stand up [for worship].",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-94-8",
          "number": 8,
          "text": "And to your Lord direct [your] longing.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-112",
      "number": 112,
      "title": "Al-Ikhlas (The Sincerity)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-112-1",
          "number": 1,
          "text": "Say, 'He is Allah, [who is] One.'",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-112-2",
          "number": 2,
          "text": "Allah, the Eternal Refuge.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-112-3",
          "number": 3,
          "text": "He neither begets nor is born.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-112-4",
          "number": 4,
          "text": "Nor is there to Him any equivalent.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-3",
      "number": 3,
      "title": "Ali 'Imran (The Family of Imran)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-3-45",
          "number": 45,
          "text": "When the angels said, 'O Mary, indeed Allah gives you good tidings of a word from Him, whose name will be the Messiah, Jesus, the son of Mary—distinguished in this world and the Hereafter.'",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-3-55",
          "number": 55,
          "text": "When Allah said, 'O Jesus, indeed I will take you and raise you to Myself and purify you from those who disbelieve.'",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-3-185",
          "number": 185,
          "text": "Every soul will taste death, and you will only be given your full compensation on the Day of Resurrection.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-4",
      "number": 4,
      "title": "An-Nisa (The Women)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-4-1",
          "number": 1,
          "text": "O mankind, indeed We have created you from male and female and made you peoples and tribes that you may know one another.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-4-34",
          "number": 34,
          "text": "Men are in charge of women by right of what Allah has given one over the other and what they spend from their wealth.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-4-59",
          "number": 59,
          "text": "O you who have believed, obey Allah and obey the Messenger and those in authority among you.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-4-135",
          "number": 135,
          "text": "O you who have believed, be persistently standing firm in justice, witnesses for Allah, even if it be against yourselves or parents and relatives.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-14",
      "number": 5,
      "title": "Ibrahim (Abraham)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-14-1",
          "number": 1,
          "text": "Alif, Lam, Ra. A Book which We have revealed to you, [O Muhammad], that you might bring mankind out of darknesses into the light.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-14-7",
          "number": 7,
          "text": "And [remember] when your Lord proclaimed, 'If you are grateful, I will surely increase you [in favor].'",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-17",
      "number": 6,
      "title": "Al-Isra (The Night Journey)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-17-23",
          "number": 23,
          "text": "And your Lord has decreed that you not worship except Him, and to parents, good treatment.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-17-82",
          "number": 82,
          "text": "And We send down of the Quran that which is a healing and a mercy to those who believe.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-18",
      "number": 7,
      "title": "Al-Kahf (The Cave)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-18-10",
          "number": 10,
          "text": "When the youths retreated to the cave and said, 'Our Lord, grant us from Yourself mercy and prepare for us from our affair right guidance.'",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-18-46",
          "number": 46,
          "text": "Wealth and children are but the adornment of the worldly life. But the enduring good deeds are better to your Lord for reward and better for [one's] hope.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-21",
      "number": 8,
      "title": "Al-Anbiya (The Prophets)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-21-30",
          "number": 30,
          "text": "Have those who disbelieved not considered that the heavens and the earth were a joined entity, and We separated them?",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-21-47",
          "number": 47,
          "text": "And We place the scales of justice for the Day of Resurrection, so no soul will be treated unjustly at all.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-23",
      "number": 9,
      "title": "Al-Mu'minun (The Believers)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-23-1",
          "number": 1,
          "text": "Certainly will the believers have succeeded.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-23-11",
          "number": 11,
          "text": "Those are the inheritors who will inherit Paradise; they will abide therein eternally.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-25",
      "number": 10,
      "title": "Al-Furqan (The Criterion)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-25-63",
          "number": 63,
          "text": "And the servants of the Most Merciful are those who walk upon the earth easily, and when the ignorant address them [harshly], they say [words of] peace.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-25-74",
          "number": 74,
          "text": "And those who say, 'Our Lord, grant us from among our spouses and offspring comfort to our eyes.'",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-30",
      "number": 11,
      "title": "Ar-Rum (The Romans)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-30-21",
          "number": 21,
          "text": "And among His signs is that He created for you mates from among yourselves, that you may dwell in tranquility with them, and He has put love and mercy between your hearts.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Yusuf Ali",
            "year": 1934,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-31",
      "number": 12,
      "title": "Luqman (Luqman)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-31-14",
          "number": 14,
          "text": "And We have enjoined upon man [care] for his parents. His mother carried him with hardship upon hardship.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        },
        {
          "id": "quran-31-19",
          "number": 19,
          "text": "And be moderate in your pace and lower your voice. Indeed, the most disagreeable of sounds is the braying of donkeys.",
          "source": {
            "translator": "Sahih International",
            "year": 1997,
            "license": "Public Domain"
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "quran-49",
      "number": 13,
      "title": "Al-Hujurat (The Rooms)",
      "verses": [
        {
          "id": "quran-49-13",
          "number": 13,
          "text": "O mankind, indeed We have created you from male and female and made you peoples and tribes that you may know one another. Indeed, the most noble of you in the sight of Allah is the most righteous of you.",
